Ney MOUTARDIER v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 8219. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Dec. 11, 1939. H. W. Vincent and Rodes K. Myers, both of Bowling Green, Ky., for appellant. Eli H. Brown, III, of Louisville, Ky., for appellee.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

This cause being called for argument, came the appellant by counsel and on his motion it is now ordered that this appeal be and the same is dismissed.
